        Most mailers and newsreaded use a monospaced font -- figlet output
        looks best when viewed with one, although modifications to the
        ouput can be made.  I recommend viewing this file with a
        monospaced font.  In the E editor, just go under Options to Set
        Font.  In EPM, use the settings notebook.  In other editors,
        there is probably also a way :-)


        This is the OS/2 port of figlet version 2.2, a  neat tool started
        by Glenn Chappell and Ian Chai, and now by John Cowan,
        to produce impressive looking lettering easily.  For example,
        it took me only a couple of seconds to make the title
        for this file.  The complete directions are in the file
        FIGLET.INF (type view figlet.inf from the command line)
        so  this README will only address issues relating to the OS/2 port
        of the program.

       ’‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘“
       œœœ OS/2 Specificities œœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœ
       ”‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘•
        The end of file signal in OS/2 is ^Z (control-Z).  When you are
        typing input for figlet from the console,  just type ^Z and ENTER
        to finish.

        The default location for figlet fonts is .\FONTS but this
        can be overridden by the -d switch.

       ’‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘“
       œœœ Displaying Fonts œœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœœ
       ”‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘‘•
        A couple  of  REXX  files, SHOWALL.CMD and SHOWONE.CMD,
        have been included to help you choose which font to use for your text.
        The text used is from a file named TEST.TXT (which you can modify with
        any text editor). Just type SHOWALL and the command file will then
        cycle through all of the figlet fonts in the .\fonts directory
        displaying the contents of TEST.TXT in that font and then pausing
        so that you can look at it.   It would be easy for you to modify the
        command files so that the  output  is  redirected to a printer or to
        add  switches  to control figlet features.

